review_blob: OK Pale Ale.  It does not hold a flame to the Best.  Leaves a weird after taste.  Not a great finish.
It is better than most of the other macros.  Definitely a beer to have tailgating before a hockey game...oh wait, hockey doesnt exist anymore.
This is an incredible wet-hopped ale.  Nice and citric.  Very nice body and color.  A must have in autumn.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Harvest Wet Hop IPA - Northern Hemisphere

review_blob: This is the best American Pale Ale ever made.  It is consistent year after year.  The way it is bottle conditioned makes it extra special.  This is an ale that really grows on you.  Definitely the standard of American Pale Ales!
